The code here feels a lot more complicated than necessary with two different functions that each invoke the other, and the callback being invoked in three different places.  Also the chunk size doesn't need to be passed around since it's a constant within any invocation of `streamParse()`.  Could we simplify to something like this:

```ts
function readChunk(oldData, newData, offset) {
  let doneReading = offset >= arrayBuffer.bytelength;
  let parts = newData.split(delim);
  parts[0] = oldData + parts[0];
  let remainder = '';
  if (!doneReading) {
    remainder = parts.pop();
  }
  for (let part of parts) {
    try {
      callback(part);
    } catch (e) {
      reject(e):
      return;
    }
  }
  if (doneReading) {
    resolve(true);
    return;
  }
  const nextChunk = new Blob([arrayBuffer.slice(offset, offset + chunkSize)]);
  const file = new FileReader();
  file.onload = (e: any) => readChunk(remainder, e.target.result, offset + chunkSize);
  file.readAsText(nextChunk);
}

readChunk('', '', 0);
```

