The logic here does not seem to be correct. We will return `kErrorNone` independent of `IsValid()` and `GetTotalLength()` checks since `error` would be set to `kErrorNone` from `SuccessOrExit(error = aMessage.Read(0, *this));` line.

I guess you copied this from similar `Ip6::Header` method. Note that we do not set the `error` in `Ip6::Header::ParseFrom()` implementation in `SuccessOrExit(aMessage.Read(0, *this));`:

```c++
Error Header::ParseFrom(const Message &aMessage)
{
    Error error = kErrorParse;

    SuccessOrExit(aMessage.Read(0, *this));
    VerifyOrExit(IsValid());
    VerifyOrExit(sizeof(Header) + GetPayloadLength() == aMessage.GetLength());

    error = kErrorNone;

exit:
    return error;
}
```

